    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study aims to investigate the effect of dexmedetomidine on oxygenation and lung mechanics
      in morbidly obese patients
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The patients of interest are morbid obese patients scheduled for bariatric surgery.
      Dexmeditomidine will be infused intraoperatively after induction of anesthesia. lung
      mechanics (dead space and compliance) as well as oxygenation (PF ratio) will be monitored
      intraoperatively and postoperatively
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
